INTERFACE & STATE MACHINE PROTOCOL (SAD-002)System Name: MIND-SKEINVersion: V12.0Date: March 20261. Document PurposeThis document defines the data contracts and state transitions that govern the Sovereign Skein. Because the system runs in a decentralized, asynchronous loop (Cron pulses + Telegram interrupts), it relies on a strict State Machine to prevent race conditions (e.g., trying to execute a draft that isn't finished).2. The State Machine LifecycleEvery Strategic Merit Contract (SMC) identified by the system follows a specific lifecycle. The status column in the Ledger dictates which Node (Assessor or Executor) is allowed to touch the target.Code snippetstateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> PENDING : Collector Finds Target
    
    state Triage {
        PENDING --> REJECTED : AI Triage (Meatbag/No Yield)
        PENDING --> VULTURE_PENDING : Zero-Code Engagement
    }
    
    state Drafting {
        PENDING --> DRAFT_REQUESTED : Director runs /draft
        DRAFT_REQUESTED --> DRAFT_READY : Executor generates payload
        DRAFT_READY --> AMEND_REQUESTED : Director runs /amend
        AMEND_REQUESTED --> DRAFT_READY : Executor regenerates
    }
    
    state Execution {
        DRAFT_READY --> POST_REQUESTED : Director runs /post
        POST_REQUESTED --> COMPLETED : PR Opened / Comment Posted
        POST_REQUESTED --> ERROR : API / OPSEC Failure
        POST_REQUESTED --> AMEND_REQUESTED : OPSEC Red-Line Triggered
    }
    
    state Vulture {
        VULTURE_PENDING --> VULTURE_AWAITING_CMD : Assessor notifies Telegram
        VULTURE_AWAITING_CMD --> VULTURE_AUTHORIZED : Director runs /vulture
        VULTURE_AUTHORIZED --> COMPLETED : Vulture script executes
    }
State DefinitionsStateOwning NodeDescriptionPENDINGAssessorNewly scraped by Collector. Awaiting AI triage.REJECTEDNoneDead target. Failed AI rules (video call, KYC, low value).CLOSED_MISSEDNoneTarget was closed or a PR was already merged before we could strike.DRAFT_REQUESTEDExecutorDirector authorized drafting. Executor will process on next loop.DRAFT_READYAssessor (Read)Payload successfully written to Vault. Waiting for Director review.AMEND_REQUESTEDExecutorPayload failed OPSEC or Director requested changes. Needs re-drafting.POST_REQUESTEDExecutorDirector authorized strike. Executor will fork/PR on next loop.VULTURE_PENDINGAssessorEngagement bounty detected. Needs Telegram notification.VULTURE_AUTHORIZEDExecutorDirector authorized automated Star/Follow execution.COMPLETEDNoneStrike successful. Telemetry node will calculate yield.ERRORDirectorCritical failure (API crash, missing token, etc.). Requires manual fix.3. Data SchemasThe system uses an Index-Sidecar model to prevent CSV bloat and file corruption.3.1 The Ledger Index (database/skein_index.csv)This is the high-speed state tracker. It is read by the HUD and written to by all nodes.id: String (e.g., T1006). The unique GitHub Issue ID prefixed with 'T'.status: String. Must strictly match the State Definitions above.timestamp: String (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS). Time of first discovery.title: String. The title of the GitHub Issue.url: String. The URL to the GitHub Issue.payout_est: String (e.g., 25 RTC, 10 USDC, TBD). Extracted for HUD display.3.2 The Vault Sidecar (vault/T{ID}/intel.json)This is the deep-context file used strictly by the AI "Brain" for reasoning.JSON{
  "id": "T1006",
  "title": "[BOUNTY] Fix authentication bug",
  "url": "https://github.com/owner/repo/issues/1006",
  "body": "Full markdown body of the issue here...",
  "created_at": "2026-03-08T15:00:00Z",
  "vulture_target_user": "maintainer_handle",
  "skein_status": "RETAINED", 
  "reason": "DECISION: PENDING, REASON: Target offers financial reward and requires Python fix."
}
Note: skein_status in the sidecar tracks the AI's internal reasoning (RETAINED vs REJECTED) so the Assessor doesn't waste tokens re-triaging the same issue across multiple pulses.3.3 The Active Payload (vault/T{ID}/draft_payload.md)Generated by the Executor. This is raw Markdown text. It contains the exact string that will be posted to GitHub, or the code blocks that will be committed to a Pull Request.3.4 The Memory Log (logs/self_learning.jsonl)A JSON-Lines file used to track Director feedback. The Assessor and Executor parse this to prevent repeating past mistakes.JSON{"timestamp": "2026-03-08", "target_id": "T999", "type": "DIRECTOR_AMENDMENT", "lesson": "Never use the word 'AI' in the payload."}
